\title{adjoint equivalence}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{riehl-2017}{RIehl}{Proposition 4.4.5}

\p{An \em{adjoint equivalence} is an [adjunction](rs-0036) whose [unit and
counit](rs-0039) are [isomorphisms](rs-0010); equivalently, it is an
[equivalence of categories](rs-0012) whose structure isomorphisms satisfy the [triangle
identities](rs-003A).}

